For every Velarro implementation task, apply SEO, AEO, GEO, SXO, AIO, accessibility, and discoverability thinking from the start.

Use legitimate visibility architecture only:
- semantic HTML
- clean heading hierarchy
- page-specific metadata
- canonical URLs
- internal linking
- breadcrumbs
- truthful structured data
- descriptive alt text
- fast responsive UX
- accessible components
- crawlable visible content

Do not create doorway pages, city/country keyword stuffing, hidden SEO text, fake localized pages, fake business locations, fake reviews, fake prices, fake products, or fake availability.

Only create city, country, language, or regional pages when there is real approved localized content and a real user/business purpose.

Use hreflang only for real localized page variants.

Structured data must describe visible approved page content only. Do not mark up content users cannot see. Do not use temporary Figma image URLs in metadata or schema.

Before claiming a page is visibility-ready, ask the Velarro Visibility Architect subagent to review it.
